author: @Oda3908
text: Why does he know those bunch of arguments for a certain method/function? Maybe most people already knew but just small tips for beginners to JupyterNB: object + . + tab will show you the methods available for a certain object, then you add a question mark after the method, run the cell, it will show you a detailed docstring for this method with decent examples. There is more information in the docstring and personally, I strongly recommend you check it out before starting to use it.
